+ * <h3>Relationship to {@link HttpParser}</h3>
+ * This handles the response side of what {@link HttpParser} formerly did. This uses the {@link
+ * HttpResponse} type directly, avoiding the deprecated {@link HttpAdapter} type. By constraining
+ * this to only response data, it is implementable as a lambda or method reference.
+ *
+ * <p>This also fixes a few problems noticed in practice with {@link HttpParser}:
+ * <ul>
+ *   <li>Implementation complexity of {@link ErrorParser}: this is now handled outside</li>
+ *   <li>Overhead of scoping the current span: {@link TraceContext} is now a parameter</li>
+ *   <li>Boxing of the HTTP status code: the integer form is now used</li>
+ * </ul>
+ *
+ * <h3>The {@link TraceContext} parameter</h3>
+ * The {@link TraceContext} parameter provides for advanced data handling, such as
